description: Temporal expressions of durations of reigns, terms, or events
Products and brands, often with model specifications, and sometimes dates
Topics, issues, or subjects being discussed, presented, provided, found, or searched, sometimes with a location or time element

The semantic concept that activates this neuron appears to be forms of the verb "to be," particularly in contexts discussing entertainment, media, or current events.  The activated words frequently include "[is]", "[was]", "[are]",  "[be]", "[been]", and contracted forms like "[‘s]", and often appear alongside discussions of movies, music, or public figures
Ratings, quantities, and names of places, people, or things
